Weatherino: Automatic outlet based on the weather conditions
------------------------------------------------------------
The program contains a meteorological station composed of a humidity, light and temperature sensor. The program sends the measurements to an LCD panel, and through the Serial interface. A plug can be controlled depending on the measured light conditions. The behavior depend on the time of the day. At night, the system will measure if the lights are off. If so, the system turns off the lamp. If the lights are on, that measn that there are people in the room, and the lamp needs to be on. During the day, the system tries to detect cloudy days. In a coudy day, the system turns on the lamp when the lights of the room are on. The lamp remains off otherwise. 